The weight reduction in the front end and the svelte wrist of the user configurable rail, make for an incredibly well balanced rifle.

The SPR features our enhanced fire control group, a Magpul MIAD pistol grip, and the new Magpul ACS stock. The fire control group, the bolt carrier and the bolt are all coated in our proprietary nickel coating that promotes permanent lubricity and allows the operator to run the gun nearly dry when the situation requires it. The piston system is our mid-length system, which provides a more direct recoil impulse for faster follow-up shots.

The SPR comes with LWRCI's new Skirmish Sights. These sights can be raised using gross motor skills and without pressing any button. The sights lock in the up position and are lowered by pressing a button on their left sides. The sights are extremely low profile and stand less than " tall when folded. All of the sharp edges have been smoothly radiused, nearly eliminating the possibility of snagging the folded sights or cutting the shooters hands when being deployed. The sights are constructed of 7075 aluminum, which is Type 3 hard coat anodized, and 4140 steel, that is treated with our Ni-corr surface conversion technology. 7075 aluminum is much harder and stronger than the 6000 series aluminum used in our competitor's sights. The bearings and detents are all industrial hard chromed. The sights are nearly impervious to corrosion. As an added benefit, all of the surfaces on the rear of the sights post and its protective wings are grooved at either 20 or 40 lines per inch to eliminate glare.

With a High Wall Single Shot Sporting Rifle from Uberti, you can relive a time when rifle shooting was more than a pastime; it was a serious business. title: For Sale:  kel tec PF9 Great Condition Everything Factory Included. Price Firm !!
location: South OKC, Central OKC, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent:
Hi there.

I Have a Great Condition Kel Tec PF9 9mm up for Sale. About 1 year old. Quite possibly the best carry gun made. Super thin and light. Low count, less then 100 rounds through the gun !!

 Done a few things to the gun to improve it. A Kel-Tec is meant to be "finished" by the owner for the most part. All modifications are easily reversible but I doubt you'd want to.

 **This gun shoots MUCH nicer than a stock factory gun.**

 - Fluff and Buffed. Gun has been broken down and deburred. Slide rails and feed ramp smoothed. Hammer surface smoothed

 - Trigger straightened, softened and shortened. Biggest complaint with this gun is the trigger shape from the factory can "pinch" larger fingers. 

 The shorter trigger is MUCH more controllable and softer to shoot. A stock replacement trigger is about 2 bucks from Kel-Tec.

 - Hogue grip installed and trimmed. Helps suck up the recoil and improve grip on this little beast.

 - +1 extended magazine bottom not only adds a round but vastly improves the gun grip.

 - Extra +1 magazine. Any defensive gun needs an extra mag. It also has the +1 extension

 - Sights and hammer painted orange. For some reason the white sights and my eyes did not play nicely. Orange is MUCH easier to see and get on target with. Orange hammer means it is much easier to stage the trigger (along with the shortened trigger) for fast accurate shots. Both are "painted" with orange nail polish. It's the type that doesn't need remover. Just "peels" off with a toothpick if you don't dig orange. You will though.

 - Shimmed rear site. Gun was accurate but this shooter always trended a touch low with it. You may be different. Shim is just a plastic spacer that you can remove if you shoot differently than I do. I'm no marksman.

 - Deburred the grip. Has some ridges on it from the factory that can hurt your hands after awhile. An hour with an emery board really smoothed things out.

 Also included:

 Kel-Tec plastic case

 Instruction booklets

title: For Sale:  LEE,RCBS,HORNADY,LYMAN,RELOADING,CASE TRIMMING TOOL
postcontent: This is a adapter I've designed that adds a case trimmer step on your power case preparation center. I was tired of prepping all my military and standard rounds on my power preparation center. Then have to use a hand case trimmer tool to trim my cases. This adapter is a real time saver. Screws in any of the power preparation station on your machine. It will also, work on rcbs and other case prep machine that use a #8-32 thread stud. Just use your lee case cutter and lee trim to length case trimmer. With the lee socket stud adapter, and a hex screwdriver to add another step to your station. Made of high strength grade aluminmum. Available in two sizes. The small adapter works with the lee small cutting tool. That will do 9mm cases up to 45 caliber. The large adapter works with the lee large cutting tool. That will do 45 caliber and above. With the right caliber lee case length trimming tool. I will include a 14 day customer satisfaction guarantee, you pay return shipping cost.
